## Overview

This document defines all UI states for error handling, empty data, and loading conditions across the DASS Health platform. All components follow a consistent design language:

- **Consistent branding** — DASS Health colors (slate, emerald, red, amber)
- **Clear messaging** — User-friendly error messages, not technical jargon
- **Recovery paths** — Every error/empty state has an action button
- **Accessibility** — Icons + text, proper contrast, keyboard navigation

### Design Principles

| Principle | Implementation |
|-----------|-----------------|
| **Clarity** | Icons + descriptive text; no error codes |
| **Recovery** | Primary action ("Retry", "Upload", "Go Home") |
| **Context** | Secondary action (navigate away, contact support) |
| **Hierarchy** | Error (red) > Warning (amber) > Info (blue) > Empty (gray) |

