### 2. ErrorFallback (Async Errors & API Failures)

**Component:** `ErrorFallback.tsx`  
**Scope:** Specific operation that failed (fetch, submit, load report)  
**Trigger:** Network error, API returns error, data validation fails

#### Layout — Full Variant

```
┌─────────────────────────────────────────────┐
│              Data Load Failed                │
│  Unable to fetch your health reports        │
│                                               │
│  [ Retry ]  [ Go Home ]                     │
└─────────────────────────────────────────────┘
```

#### Layout — Compact Variant

```
┌─────────────────────────┐
│  ⚠️  Failed to load.     │
│      Retry?             │
│      Retry →            │
└─────────────────────────┘
```

#### Props

```typescript
interface ErrorFallbackProps {
  title?: string;                    // Heading (default: "Error")
  message: string;                   // Main error description
  icon?: string;                     // Emoji (default: "⚠️")
  action?: {                         // Primary CTA
    label: string;
    onClick: () => void;
  };
  secondary?: {                      // Secondary CTA
    label: string;
    onClick: () => void;
  };
  variant?: "compact" | "full";     // Layout size (default: "full")
  className?: string;                // Tailwind overrides
}
```

#### Common Error Messages

| Scenario | Title | Message | Icon | Action |
|----------|-------|---------|------|--------|
| **API timeout** | Request timed out | Connection took too long. Please try again. | ⏱️ | Retry |
| **Network down** | Connection lost | Check your internet and try again. | 🌐 | Retry |
| **Resource not found** | Not found | This report no longer exists. | 🔍 | Go Home |
| **Permission denied** | Access denied | You don't have permission to view this. | 🔒 | Go Home |
| **Server error** | Server error | Something went wrong on our end. Please try later. | ⚙️ | Report Issue / Go Home |
| **Invalid data** | Data error | The uploaded file isn't valid. | 📄 | Upload New / Go Home |

#### Usage

```tsx
import { ErrorFallback } from "@/components/ui/ErrorFallback";
import { useAsync } from "@/lib/hooks/useAsync";

function ReportsList() {
  const { state, data, error, execute } = useAsync(
    async () => {
      const res = await fetch("/api/reports");
      if (!res.ok) throw new Error(`${res.status}`);
      return res.json();
    },
    true  // Execute on mount
  );

  if (state === "error") {
    return (
      <ErrorFallback
        title="Failed to load reports"
        message={error?.message || "Try again in a moment"}
        action={{ label: "Retry", onClick: execute }}
        secondary={{ label: "Go Home", onClick: () => navigate("/") }}
      />
    );
  }

  return <div>{/* Success content */}</div>;
}
```

#### QA Test Cases

- ✅ **Compact variant:** Verify smaller layout in card scenarios
- ✅ **Full variant:** Verify centered full-page layout
- ✅ **Action button:** Click retry; verify callback fires
- ✅ **Secondary button:** Click; verify navigation works
- ✅ **Custom messages:** Test with different error scenarios
- ✅ **Icon override:** Custom emoji renders correctly
- ✅ **Accessibility:** Tab navigation, ARIA labels

