## Loading States

### LoadingSkeleton Component

**Component:** `LoadingSkeleton.tsx`  
**Scope:** Content is fetching; show placeholder  
**Trigger:** `state === "loading"` in useAsync/useFetch

#### Skeleton Variants

| Variant | Use Case | Duration |
|---------|----------|----------|
| **DashboardSkeleton** | Full dashboard loading | 1–3 seconds |
| **ReportListSkeleton** | Report list items | 1–2 seconds |
| **AlertCardSkeleton** | Alert cards | 500ms–1s |
| **ChatMessageSkeleton** | AI response generating | Streaming (indeterminate) |

#### Layout

```
Skeleton lines pulse with fade animation:
┌─────────────────────────────────────┐
│ ▓▓▓▓▓▓▓ (pulsing)                   │
│ ▓▓▓▓▓▓▓▓▓ (pulsing)                 │
│                                      │
│ ▓▓▓▓▓ (pulsing)   ▓▓▓ (pulsing)     │
│ ▓▓▓▓▓▓▓▓ (pulsing)                  │
└─────────────────────────────────────┘
```

#### Spinner Component

Used for smaller, in-line loading (chat messages, data submission).

```tsx
<div className="flex items-center gap-2">
  <Spinner size="sm" />
  <span className="text-sm text-slate-400">Generating response...</span>
</div>
```

#### Props

```typescript
interface SpinnerProps {
  size?: "sm" | "md" | "lg";   // Icon size
}

interface LoadingSkeletonProps {
  type?: "dashboard" | "report" | "alert" | "chat";
}
```

#### Usage

```tsx
function ReportsList() {
  const { state, data } = useAsync(() => fetchReports(), true);

  // Loading state
  if (state === "loading") {
    return <ReportListSkeleton />;
  }

  // Error state
  if (state === "error") {
    return <ErrorFallback message="Failed to load reports" />;
  }

  // Empty state
  if (data?.length === 0) {
    return <EmptyState message="No reports yet" />;
  }

  // Success state
  return <div>{/* Render reports */}</div>;
}
```

#### QA Test Cases

- ✅ **Pulse animation:** Verify smooth fade in/out
- ✅ **Duration:** Verify skeleton displays until `state` changes
- ✅ **Responsive:** Content placeholder matches actual content width
- ✅ **No interaction:** User can't click skeleton (pointer-events: none)
- ✅ **Accessibility:** Screen reader announces "Loading..."

