## QA Checklist

### Visual Regression Testing

- [ ] **ErrorBoundary throws** — Error UI renders, development stack visible
- [ ] **ErrorFallback compact** — Inline error in card, smaller spacing
- [ ] **ErrorFallback full** — Centered, large error page
- [ ] **EmptyState default** — Large icon, centered, button below
- [ ] **EmptyState compact** — Inline, smaller, link-style button
- [ ] **LoadingSkeleton** — Pulse animation smooth, matches content width
- [ ] **Spinner** — Rotates smoothly, size variants work
- [ ] **Responsive mobile** — All states adapt to small screens

### Functional Testing

#### ErrorBoundary

- [ ] Catching errors prevents full page crash
- [ ] "Try again" button resets component state
- [ ] "Go Home" button navigates to `/`
- [ ] Development mode shows stack trace
- [ ] Production mode hides technical details
- [ ] Nested ErrorBoundaries work correctly

#### ErrorFallback

- [ ] Retry action triggers callback
- [ ] Secondary action navigates correctly
- [ ] Custom title/message render
- [ ] Custom icons display
- [ ] Variants (compact/full) have correct layout

#### EmptyState

- [ ] Icon renders (emoji or React element)
- [ ] Message and subtext display
- [ ] Action button works
- [ ] Without action, no button appears
- [ ] Variants (compact/default) adapt layout

#### LoadingSkeleton

- [ ] Skeleton animates smoothly
- [ ] Disappears when state changes to success/error
- [ ] All variants (dashboard, report, alert, chat) display correctly

### Accessibility Testing

- [ ] All buttons have `aria-label`
- [ ] Keyboard navigation (Tab) works
- [ ] Focus visible on buttons
- [ ] Screen reader announces states
- [ ] Color not only indicator (icons + text)
- [ ] Sufficient contrast (WCAG AA minimum)

### Responsive Testing

- [ ] Mobile (320px): Layout stacks, no overflow
- [ ] Tablet (768px): Balanced layout
- [ ] Desktop (1920px): Full layout, consistent spacing

### Performance Testing

- [ ] Skeleton animates at 60fps
- [ ] Spinner renders without jank
- [ ] Error/empty components load instantly
- [ ] No memory leaks when components unmount

