## Testing Scenarios

### Scenario 1: User Uploads First Report

```
START
  ↓
Attach file
  ↓
SUBMITTING... (LoadingSkeleton in dialog)
  ↓
✓ SUCCESS
  ↓
Reports page transitions from EmptyState → SUCCESS with new report
```

**QA checks:**
- ✅ Dialog shows loading spinner during upload
- ✅ On success, dialog closes
- ✅ Reports page refreshes
- ✅ New report appears in list

### Scenario 2: Network Error During Report Fetch

```
Reports page
  ↓
LOADING (DashboardSkeleton)
  ↓
❌ NETWORK ERROR
  ↓
ErrorFallback displays
  ↓
User clicks "Retry"
  ↓
LOADING again
  ↓
✓ SUCCESS (recovers)
```

**QA checks:**
- ✅ Skeleton appears initially
- ✅ Network error shows ErrorFallback
- ✅ Retry button re-fetches
- ✅ Success renders reports

### Scenario 3: No Alerts / Empty State

```
Alerts page (no new alerts)
  ↓
LOADING (skeleton)
  ↓
✓ SUCCESS but empty array
  ↓
EmptyState displays
  ↓
User clicks "View Archived"
  ↓
Navigate to alerts?filter=archived
```

**QA checks:**
- ✅ Skeleton appears
- ✅ Empty array triggers EmptyState
- ✅ Action button navigates correctly

### Scenario 4: Error within Error Boundary

```
Dashboard component throws error
  ↓
React propagates error up
  ↓
ErrorBoundary catches it
  ↓
Error UI renders with reset option
  ↓
User clicks "Try again"
  ↓
Component re-mounts, no error → content renders
```

**QA checks:**
- ✅ Error prevents render crash
- ✅ Error UI shows safely
- ✅ Reset works, component remounts

